All right, so what does a successful NetSuite Orion implementation look
like? And as I mentioned, these are slides that I put together myself.
These are me thinking about over the years doing implementations and
working in organizations and what does it actually, what are the
necessary ingredients for us to be successful during this
implementation? And there\'s a number of things that we\'re going to
review. But from my standpoint, when I think about this, what I really
am looking to accomplish for you. Pivot from proprio, from Us to you is
we want to see operational excellence for your organization. So we want
to find ways to smooth out your day to day operations. We really want to
be careful that we\'re not introducing any business disruptions because
you all have your day jobs.

**\
14:38**\
Marcus Dallacqua\
And so it\'s one of the reasons why we don\'t go super fast with these
implementations because we do this all day long, but you guys have your
day jobs. And so we want to be careful about the impact to your
organization. Want to always keep our eye on those activities that are
revenue generating for you. So you\'re going to see that we\'re not
going to push you to overbook yourself. We recognize that, especially
ourselves being previous customers and having our own businesses running
in NetSuite, we understand that complete data migration, you know,
you\'re coming off of a number of systems and so we have to be really
careful and thoughtful about what we\'re going to bring over and how
we\'re going to bring it over and when we\'re going to bring it over and
that\'s really important.

**\
15:22**\
Marcus Dallacqua\
And then we also want to make sure that you\'re fully trained. We have a
really, I think, unique philosophy when it comes to netsuite and really
what our goal is to see you to be self reliant on the platform. We
don\'t want to just get you in the system, turn the key, start the
ignition and walk away and have you kind of figured out as you go. And
we also don\'t want you to be dependent on us. Again, this comes from
our customer perspective where we don\'t want to have to keep going back
to an organization and paying them money to write a report for us or do
something that\'s somewhat basic in the system.

**\
16:00**\
Marcus Dallacqua\
Well, we want to make sure that we transfer that knowledge to you and
